  "text": "I'm going to make a statement and then let you correct it if I've made any errors. This is the statement. Creation is a single entity or unity. If only a single entity exists, then the only concept of service is service to self. If this single entity subdivides, then the concept of service of one of its parts to the other part is born. From this concept springs the quality of service to self or to others. It would seem that as the logos subdivided, parts would select each orientation, as individualized entities emerge in space-time, then I would assume they have polarity. Is this statement correct? I am ra this statement is a quite a perceptive and a correct until the final phrase in which we note that the polarities begin to be explored only at the point when a third density entity becomes aware of the possibility of a choice between the concept or distortion of a service to self or a service to others. This marks the end of what you may call the unself conscious or innocent phase of conscious awareness.",
